üìå Objective:
Perform the following using HiveQL:

Create, drop, alter tables

Load data into tables

Create external Hive tables

üîß Step-by-Step HiveQL Code
üóÉÔ∏è 1. Create a Table
sql
Copy
Edit
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS employee (
  emp_id INT,
  name STRING,
  dept STRING
)
ROW FORMAT DELIMITED
FIELDS TERMINATED BY ',';
üîÑ 2. Alter the Table
sql
Copy
Edit
ALTER TABLE employee ADD COLUMNS (designation STRING);
‚ùå 3. Drop the Table
sql
Copy
Edit
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS employee;
üì• 4. Load Data into Table
First, prepare a CSV file (employee.csv):

Copy
Edit
101,John,Sales,Manager
102,Anita,HR,HR Executive
103,Ravi,IT,Developer
Upload it to HDFS:

bash
Copy
Edit
hdfs dfs -put /local/path/employee.csv /user/hive/warehouse/
Then run this in Hive:

sql
Copy
Edit
LOAD DATA INPATH '/user/hive/warehouse/employee.csv' INTO TABLE employee;
üåê 5. Create External Table
sql
Copy
Edit
CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE IF NOT EXISTS employee_ext (
  emp_id INT,
  name STRING,
  dept STRING,
  designation STRING
)
ROW FORMAT DELIMITED
FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','
STORED AS TEXTFILE
LOCATION '/user/hive/external/employee/';
Copy the CSV to that HDFS location:

bash
Copy
Edit
hdfs dfs -mkdir -p /user/hive/external/employee
hdfs dfs -put /local/path/employee.csv /user/hive/external/employee/
